Sentencas: In this paper, three composite electrolytes (Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9/Na2CO3) SDC, (Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9/ Na2CO3) GDC and (La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta/Na2CO3) LSGM have been studied to review the effect of Na2CO3, present as second phase, and effect of Ni support, sintering and pressure for dry pressing for fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes

Sentencas: The electrolytes were prepared through a co-precipitation method.
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes

Sentencas: Different techniques were used to characterize the prepared electrolytes.
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes

Sentencas: The crystal structures were determined using x-ray diffraction (XRD) and structural morphologies were analyzed through scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes

Sentencas: The four probe dc conductivity and two probe AC impedance analysis were carried out in open air.
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes

Sentencas: The fuel cell performance was determined with and without Ni support on anode side which resulted in a considerable difference in obtained peak power densities.
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes

Sentencas: It is suggested that prepared electrolytes can find potential applications in low temperatures Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Nickel foam anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite electrolytes
